Locations of other presidents' papers

Prior to the establishment of the formalized NARA system, the papers of many presidents found homes in a variety of institutions, reflecting a more decentralized approach to historical preservation. For instance, the extensive papers of both [Grover Cleveland](/Grover_Cleveland) and [Woodrow Wilson](/Woodrow_Wilson) were entrusted to [Princeton University](/Princeton_University), where they are meticulously preserved and made available for scholarly research at the distinguished [Seeley G. Mudd Manuscript Library](/Seeley_G._Mudd_Manuscript_Library). Similarly, the [Theodore Roosevelt Association](/Theodore_Roosevelt_Association) undertook the considerable effort of collecting [Theodore Roosevelt](/Theodore_Roosevelt)'s vast papers, subsequently donating them to his alma mater, [Harvard University](/Harvard_University), in 1943. These invaluable documents now reside across its Widener and [Houghton libraries](/Houghton_Library), providing a comprehensive resource for studying his dynamic career. &#91;34&#93;

The papers of [James Buchanan](/James_Buchanan), a president whose term was fraught with pre-Civil War tensions, were bequeathed to the venerable [Historical Society of Pennsylvania](/Historical_Society_of_Pennsylvania) in [Philadelphia](/Philadelphia), where they continue to offer critical insights into that tumultuous period. In an ongoing effort to centralize and make accessible the records of another pivotal figure, The Papers of [Andrew Jackson](/Andrew_Jackson) project, sponsored by the [University of Tennessee at Knoxville](/University_of_Tennessee_at_Knoxville), is dedicated to compiling Jackson's papers, primarily in a microfilm edition. &#91;35&#93; A similar archival endeavor saw a microfilm edition of [Martin Van Buren](/Martin_Van_Buren)'s papers produced at [Pennsylvania State University](/Pennsylvania_State_University) in 1987, while a more contemporary digital edition of the [Papers of Martin Van Buren](/Papers_of_Martin_Van_Buren) is currently being developed at [Cumberland University](/Cumberland_University), reflecting the shift towards digital accessibility. &#91;36&#93; Concurrently, a significant project is underway on behalf of [James Madison](/The_Papers_of_James_Madison), a collaborative effort spearheaded by the Universities of Virginia and Chicago, aiming to comprehensively document the life and contributions of the Father of the Constitution.

For many presidents, particularly those who served before the systematic development of the NARA system, substantial collections of their papers and artifacts may still be found dispersed across multiple private and public institutions, creating a complex web for researchers to navigate. &#91;37&#93; Until the [Barack Obama Presidential Center](/Barack_Obama_Presidential_Center)'s physical library is fully operational and ready for service, his presidential papers are being securely held in a dedicated facility in [Hoffman Estates, Illinois](/Hoffman_Estates,_Illinois). These materials, with the expected exception of classified documents, have been made available to the public through the [Freedom of Information Act (FOIA)](/Freedom_of_Information_Act_(United_States)) since 2023, ensuring a degree of transparency even during this transitional phase.

